<HEADLINE>
MORE OVERSEAS TAIWAN BUSINESSES INVESTING AT HOME: MOEA
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 16 (CNA) 03/16/07  20:30:29 (By Lilian Wu)
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Economic Affairs (MOEA) will continue to assist
overseas Taiwan businessmen to invest at home.
</P>
<P>
MOEA officials made the remarks following the release of
statistics showing that three overseas Taiwan businessmen have
returned to Taiwan and invested NT$190 million (US$5.75 million)
since January.
</P>
<P>
They noted that since last September, overseas Taiwan businessmen
have made an accumulated NT$7.02 billion-worth of domestic
investment.
</P>
<P>
They said that under a "Mega Investment, Mega Warmth" economic
stimulus project recently unveiled by the Executive Yuan,
soliciting overseas Taiwan businessmen has been one of the major
tasks.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has kept abreast of 136 such potential investment
projects, among which 73 manufacturers are set to invest locally,
while another 63 are still assessing their options.
</P>
<P>
Among the 73 manufacturers who are set to return, most are in the
electric and electronic manufacturing, machinery manufacturing
and chemical manufacturing sectors.
</P>
<P>
In terms of region, manufacturers returning from China topped the
list at 34, followed by the United States at 13, while there are
also Taiwanese businessmen in Hong Kong, Thailand and Malaysia
planning to invest at home.
</P>
